To visualise data, I'm using the tidyverse extension for R. You must run `library(tidyverse)` each time you want to run the programme.

To load starwars dataset:
```r
view(starwars)
```

To find the class of the column
```r
print(class(df$name))

#Specifically for name column
print(class(starwars$name))
```

#Filter by height
```r
?filter
filter(starwars, height > 100)
```

#Defining new variable
```r
tall_height <- filter(starwars, height > 100)
```

#Changing height from metric to imperial
```r
imp_height <- mutate(starwars, height = 0.0328084 * height)
```

#Another way to do it
```r
imp_height <- starwars %>%
  mutate(height = 0.0328084 * height)
```

#Grouping by variables
```r
starwars %>%
  group_by(eye_color) %>%
  summarise(mean(mass))
```
